        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "Done — first commit reverts `buftypes` (EDIT: nvm this was already merged upstream), second adds help to the default guard. \r\n\r\nI agree we don't need a per-config field for this. Further, I think the `buftype==''` warrants more discussion and the `get_configs()` solution is interesting.\r\n\r\nBut... I think helpfile is truly a special case that warrants a _separate_ solution. It *is* indeed a real file and that's not ambiguous and that adding this exception clause is the right choice.",
